<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> Dennis Kimbro <i>Think and Grow Rich: a Black Choice</i>, p. 6, Random House Inc., 1992 <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780449219980" class="internal">ISBN 978-0449219980</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> Brad Kearns <i>How Tiger Does It</i>, p. 24-5, McGraw-Hill Professional, 2008 <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780071545648" class="internal">ISBN 978-0071545648</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=c86H36mgiM4C&amp;pg=PP&amp;&amp;dq=According+to+Napoleon+Hill,+98%25+..." class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=c86H36mgiM4C&amp;pg=PP&amp;&amp;dq=According+to+Napoleon+Hill,+98%25+..." rel="nofollow"><i>Think and Grow Rich</i> by Napoleon Hill</a> p. viii</li>
